<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 24 at 6:52PM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...Showers producing Hail up to 1/2 inch diameter moving across
eastern Ashe, Wilkes, Alleghany counties in North Carolina, and
Grayson and Carroll counties in Virginia...
At 647 PM EDT, Doppler radar indicated A line of showers with
isolated thunder producing 1/4 to 1/2 inch hail will move across
eastern Ashe, Wilkes, Alleghany counties in North Carolina and
Grayson and Carroll counties in VA, including the independent city
of Galax...through 730 PM EDT.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Galax...
Hillsville...
Sparta...
Independence...
Fries...
Traphill...
and Mc Grady.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
